{
  "text": "Male 5-to 7-week-old C57BL/6 (B6), NOD/ShiLtJ (NOD), and B6.129P2-Il10 tm1Ggn (IL10KO) mice were purchased from Jackson Laboratory (Bar Harbor, ME) as required. For all experiments, 4 to 5 animals were used per group (unless otherwise stated). Experiments were performed in duplicate (N 5 2) with no exclusion of animals. No randomization was performed between mice, as all comparisons were made directly between genetically identical commercially obtained animals. All experiments were conducted in male mice, as the disease condition being studied is restricted to men. Experimental prostatitis was induced in specific mice by subcutaneous injection of rat prostate homogenate at a 1:1 ratio with TiterMax adjuvant behind the right shoulder of the animals. After this, referred allodynia responses were measured by von Frey force filament behavioral testing for pelvic tactile allodynia, as described. [CITATION_1] Testing was performed before EAP induction (baseline) and then every 7 days unless otherwise stated. Results were calculated as a percentage change above baseline and for each von Frey filament of increasing force per group individually, values were averaged across experimental groups. Behavioral testing was performed after treatments (with bacteria or LTA) in a blinded manner with no knowledge of treated vs untreated groups. For these treatment experiments, pelvic tactile allodynia responses were displayed using day 21 pretreatment values and all testing values subsequent to this. After 28 days of EAP (unless otherwise stated), mice were killed and relevant tissues removed. Prostate and bladder tissues were dissociated using collagenase/DNase buffer (1640-RPMI [Corning] containing 10% FCS [HyClone], 0.1 mL/mL DNase [Thermo Scientific], and 1 mg/mL collagenase D [Roche]) and shaking for 2 hours at 37\u02daC. Tissues were then made into single cell suspensions by passing through 0.2-mm mesh filter membranes and washing with 2% FCS (HyClone) in PBS (Gibco). For splenic and iliac lymph node tissues, single cell suspensions were generated without collagenase treatment.",
  "citation_candidates": [
